11:17.790 --> 11:20.770
it actually encourages me to ask you the question.

11:20.990 --> 11:25.790
Because, you know, when I hear the framing of what is happening in Israel,

11:26.370 --> 11:31.910
where a genocidal terror organization holding two million civilians in Gaza

11:31.910 --> 11:37.270
alongside all those civilians in Israel that were targeted on Saturday morning

11:37.270 --> 11:42.510
as we were in our synagogues on a Sabbath morning and a holiday in Israel,

11:43.030 --> 11:49.590
5,000 rockets launched at Israeli civilians from densely populated areas in Gaza,

11:49.950 --> 11:54.670
each rocket a double war crime and a violation of international humanitarian law.

11:54.670 --> 12:04.450
When I think of the massacre targeting Jews that indiscriminately shot 260 at least young partygoers

12:04.450 --> 12:12.150
on that very day of the holiday, when I think of the anti-Semitic terror organization Hamas

12:12.670 --> 12:19.590
actually designated as a terror organization funded and supported by a genocidal regime in Iran

12:19.590 --> 12:28.150
holding its own civilians in Iran in the same way that Gaza, in the same way that ISIS,

12:28.370 --> 12:31.910
in the same way that 9-11 was a wake-up call to the West,

12:32.430 --> 12:39.690
that genocidal terror cannot be allowed to dictate the way that sovereign democratic countries conduct ourselves.

12:40.050 --> 12:44.250
So I would turn the question to you if this were happening anywhere else in the world,

12:44.510 --> 12:48.090
not only for Israel's right to defend its civilians,

12:48.090 --> 12:51.930
but Israel's indeed responsibility to defend its civilians,

12:52.250 --> 12:59.570
where the majority of those targeted over the last 48 hours are indeed civilians

13:00.090 --> 13:07.990
and holding families of Holocaust survivors being abducted into the Gaza Strip

13:07.990 --> 13:11.910
of entire families being butchered in their homes

13:11.910 --> 13:20.370
and to hear the way that the framing, that BBC enables this situation is actually part and parcel

13:20.370 --> 13:25.670
of what enables genocidal terror to control and to continue to dictate the discourse.

13:26.110 --> 13:33.770
Well, I think you'll find that we're talking to as many different people with as many perspectives on this as we can.

13:33.970 --> 13:40.090
I asked you how Israelis were feeling and I got a sense from you of the anger there is

13:40.090 --> 13:46.190
and the sadness too. No, there is no anger. We are fighting for our lives. There is no anger. Let it be clear.

13:46.830 --> 13:54.450
You said that this is like Israel's 9-11. Is that because of the shock that this was able to happen?

13:55.290 --> 13:59.590
It's not just because of this shock. It's because of the same modus operandi.

14:00.170 --> 14:06.610
This is a terror organization listed as such in most of the countries that are listening to us at the moment.

14:06.610 --> 14:13.470
Terror is not a moral equivalency to a sovereign country that must defend its citizens from terror.

14:14.110 --> 14:19.990
You cannot speak about both sides if you actually want to understand what Israelis are feeling.

14:20.370 --> 14:26.570
There is no both sides when a terror organization ravages civilian areas,

14:27.010 --> 14:31.450
enters under the guise of 5,000 rockets targeting those civilians,

14:31.450 --> 14:38.490
breaking barriers, that there is a fence. There has not been any occupation of Gaza since 2005.

14:39.230 --> 14:41.830
There has been a blockade though hasn't there of Gaza?

14:41.910 --> 14:49.570
No, there is no blockade because there are thousands, thousands of workers entering Gaza every day to work in Israel.

14:50.210 --> 14:54.910
There are thousands of truckloads. There is electricity and water still being supplied.

14:55.090 --> 15:00.270
Although Hamas has responsibility for the civilians in Gaza because that's who was elected

15:00.270 --> 15:05.450
to reign over Gaza and there is a responsibility of the international community

15:05.450 --> 15:14.970
and of all those that cherish life and liberty to hold Hamas to account for holding those two million civilians in Gaza hostage to their war crimes

15:14.970 --> 15:17.430
not only on Israel but on Gaza civilians.

15:18.130 --> 15:20.230
How do you think the Israeli military should respond then?

15:20.350 --> 15:25.490
We've seen a total of more than 500 air strikes over the weekend.

15:25.510 --> 15:28.010
How do you think the Israeli military should, how do you think any other countries...

15:28.010 --> 15:30.230
Well, my job is to ask questions and not answer them.

15:30.810 --> 15:36.550
Well, I'm wondering what you think any country must do in order to protect its civilians when they're being attacked, including as we speak,

15:37.170 --> 15:43.050
in their homes, including as we speak. There is an ongoing war here with genocidal terror.

15:43.590 --> 15:52.150
This is not two countries fighting each other. A genocidal terror organization, ISIS if you will, 9-11, needs moral clarity.

15:52.550 --> 15:56.330
And this is not just about Jews around the world who are now under attack.

15:56.330 --> 15:58.870
Obviously, to my question then, how do you think the military should respond?

15:59.010 --> 16:09.830
There's been speculation there might be a ground invasion of Gaza, although we're told there are dozens of Israeli hostages in Gaza at the moment.

16:10.250 --> 16:14.010
Do you think a ground invasion is the way for the Israeli government to go?

16:14.750 --> 16:21.870
There are dozens of Israeli hostages and many of them are civilians that were abducted, many of them raped,

16:21.870 --> 16:26.070
many of them paraded around the streets of Gaza and celebrated.

16:27.070 --> 16:36.730
And the Israeli IDF will do everything that it needs to do to protect as it must the citizens of the state of Israel under attack as we speak.

16:37.690 --> 16:49.490
And every country that cherishes life and liberty must protect its citizens from an ongoing onslaught, massacre of its civilians.

16:49.490 --> 16:53.910
And those hostages that have been held are being held by a genocidal terror organization.

16:54.090 --> 17:06.490
And I want to make it very clear alongside two Israeli deceased soldiers and two civilians that have been held by the same genocidal terror organization in a nine-year standing violation of international law and human rights.

17:06.490 --> 17:23.490
And each one of those civilians and every one of our countries must call for the immediate and unconditional return because it is countries supporting Gaza and enabling Hamas, a genocidal terror organization, to hold those civilians hostage as we speak.

17:23.990 --> 17:30.430
And what the IDF will have to do and the state of Israel will have to do in its existential war is not just about the state of Israel.

17:30.570 --> 17:32.190
I want to make it very clear to your listeners.

17:32.190 --> 17:35.690
Mikal Karkler-Vunch, we've got to leave it there. Thanks for joining us.

17:36.690 --> 17:40.270
